Oh where, oh where can my baby be?
The Lord took her away from me
She's gone to Heaven so I got to be good
So I can see my baby when I leave this world

We were out on a date in my daddy's car
We hadn't driven very far
There in the road, straight ahead
A car was stalled, the engine was dead
I couldn't stop, so I swerved to the right
I'll never forget the sound that night
The screaming tires, the busting glass
The painful scream that I heard last

Oh where, oh where can my baby be?
The Lord took her away from me
She's gone to Heaven, so I got to be good
So I can see my baby when I leave this world

When I woke up the rain as pouring down
There were people standing all around
Somthing warm flowing through my eyes
But somehow I found my baby that night
I lifted her head, she looked at me and said
Hold me darling just a little while
I held her close, I kissed her our last kiss
I found the love that I knew I had missed
Well, now she's gone even though I hold her tight
I lost my love, my life, that night

Oh where, oh where can my baby be? 
The Lord took her away from me
She's gone to Heaven so I got to be good
So I can see my baby when I leave this world

Dont be fooled by me. Dont be fooled by the mask i wear. For i wear a mask, i wear a thousand masks, masks that im afraid to take off, and none of them is me. Pretending is an art that is second nature with me, but dont be fooled. ....I give the impression that im secure, that all is sunny and unruffled with me, within as well as without; that confidence is my name and coolness is my game; that the waters are calm and that im in command and i need no one. But dont believe it; please dont. I dily chatter with you in the suave tones of surface talk. I tell you everything thats really nothing, nothing of whats crying within me. So when im going through my routine, dont be fooled by what im saying. please listen carefully and try to hear what im not saying; what id like to be able to say; what, for survival, i need to say but i cant say. I dislike the hiding. Honestly i do. I dislike the superficial phony games im playing. Id really like to be genuine, spontaneous, and me; but you have to help me. You have to help me by holding out your hand, even when thats the last thing i seem to want or need. Each time you are kind and gentle and encouraging, eachtime you try to understand because you really care, my heart begins to grow wings. very small wings. Very feeble wings. But wings. With your sensitivity and sympathy and your power of understanding, i can make it. You can breathe life into me. It will not be easy for you. A long conviction of worthlessness builds up strong walls. But love is strounger than strong walls, and therin lies my hope. Please try to beat down those walls with firm hands, but with gentle hands, for a child is very sensitive, and i am a child

i am updating due to popular demand...i dont have much to say...i hate school still...i only consistently like everyday more than just hi talk to one person...does that even make sence...? o well it does to me...so yea...im finding it hard to think of something to write...o i got it...ill explain my day...in full detail...haha...ok...so today...i woke up at 6:58 2 mins before the alarm goes off...so i used that time to go to the bathroom(*brushes hand through grass* haha kellie) ok then i got dressed...and i straightened me hair... theni put on a white roxy shirt, jeans, and my faded navy blue roxy shoes, my 2 necklaces and rings...then i put on rice flower and shea scented lotion then i o i forgot the part about me putting on socks...cant forget that...ok then i put my gym clothes in my backpack then i put on eye liner and mascara...then deodorant...then..i went upstairs...ate some lucky charms..:) then i made a pbj sandwhich then brushed my teeth then i got my back pack and books and walked out the door...at 8 oclock like exactly lol ok...then got in my sisters car drove for 30 mins to school got there walked the long journey from the parking lot to the school and stood outside till the bell rang...went to my locker...put my books in there...( i actually found a good system for the locker! yay) ok back on track...put my science and algebra crap inthere...then i saw cute guy in journalism and so we talked while walking to class...then..i went to journalism took notes on journalism history what fun...then i walked to english and we went to the media center and listened to the "orientation of your media center" and we actually frickin had to take notes and her check them and then have a test on it tomorrow...wtf mate? ok well then went to gym and did the long jump and sit ups...havent talked to will yet...lol if any of you were wondering...then i went to lunch and ate my pbj sandwhich that i made...and had gatorade...then i went to art and did stupid still life...god i didnt know how much i sucked at drawing a pot of flowers a conch shell...i think thats what it is and an apple...god it sucked...o well...then i went to my locker before math and then i went to math...and yea..it was math..nothing like math last year though...:(...k then...i went to science...and that was stupid ppl dont get conversions in that class god there so dumb o well...then i went to my locker and met ashley and we walked to the car...then we went home...i ate some cheetos then i had to clean my room...then i did some of my math hw...then left for pitching got back at 830 man that was long and hard...o well...then i came home took a shower...then i came to the computer and talked to ppl and now im writing this...well that is all for my day

-kristin
